rgb_hsl.color

Class HSLColor

  • java.lang.Object
    • rgb_hsl.color.Color
      • rgb_hsl.color.HSLColor

  • public class HSLColor
extends Color
    Subclass of Color. Used for describing a color by hue, saturation, and lightness.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Noah Teshima

    • Constructor Detail

      • HSLColor

        public HSLColor()
        Default constructor. When invoked, the current instance is set to have a hue of 0, a saturation of 0, and a lightness of 0, resulting in a pure black.

      • HSLColor

        public HSLColor(HSLColor color)
        Create an HSL color with the same values as the given HSLColor reference.
        Parameters:
        color - HSLColor reference containing the HSL values to copy.

      • HSLColor

        public HSLColor(int hue,
                double saturation,
                double lightness)
        Set the hue, saturation, and lightness values to their corresponding parameters.
        Parameters:
        hue - integer value containing the degree of the new hue.
        saturation - double value containing the percentage of saturation.
        lightness - double value containing the percentage of lightness.

      • setHue

        public void setHue(int hue)
        Set the hue of the current instance. Takes values in range [0, 360], inclusive. However, in the instance where the hue is not in the given range, modulus will be used in order to ensure the resulting hue will be in the range [0, 360].
        Parameters:
        hue - integer value containing the degree of the new hue.

      • getHue

        public int getHue()
        Get the hue of the current instance. The resulting hue is guaranteed to be in the range [0, 360].
        Returns:
        integer value containing the degree of hue.

      • incrementHue

        public void incrementHue(int degrees)
        Increment the hue of the current color by the specified amount. If a negative value is specified, the hue is decremented instead.
        Parameters:
        degrees - integer value containing the number of degrees to increment or decrement the hue by.

      • setSaturation

        public void setSaturation(double saturation)
        Set the saturation of the current instance on the range [0, 1], inclusive. If the given saturation is outside of these bounds, it is set to the closest boundary on this range.
        Parameters:
        saturation - double value containing the new saturation.

      • getSaturation

        public double getSaturation()
        Get the saturation of the current instance. The saturation is guaranteed to always be on the range [0, 1], inclusive.
        Returns:
        double value containing the current saturation

      • setLightness

        public void setLightness(double lightness)
        Set the lightness of the current instance on the range [0 to 1], inclusive. If the given lightness is outside of these bounds, it is set to the closest boundary on this range.
        Parameters:
        lightness - double value containing the new lightness.

      • getLightness

        public double getLightness()
        Accessor method used to get the lightness of the current instance. The saturation is guaranteed to always be on the range [0, 1], inclusive.
        Returns:
        double value containing the current lightness

      • getGreen

        public int getGreen()
        Get the amount of green in the HSL color. The amount of green is guaranteed to be on the range [0, 255] inclusive.
        Returns:
        integer value containing the amount of green in the current HSL color.

      • getBlue

        public int getBlue()
        Get the amount of blue in the HSL color. The amount of blue is guaranteed to be on the range [0, 255] inclusive.
        Returns:
        integer value containing the amount of blue in the current HSL color.

      • getRGBColor

        public RGBColor getRGBColor()
        Get the corresponding color in an RGB color space. This is a linear transformation between RGB and HSL color spaces, and represents the equivalent form in RGB space.
        Returns:
        RGBColor object that corresponds to the current instance's HSL values.
